# `tp-ui-core-font-face`

## Font usage

In existing projects our webfont Avenir will already be loading. To change weights you reference the weight value. Your options depend on the what the project is loading but usually at least `400`, `500`, and `600` are options.

```scss
.foo {
    font-weight: 500;
}
```

To use our Avenir font on Thumbtack projects:

1. Reference the font weights and styles to use in your project's variables file
2. Add the tracking script according to the terms of our license
3. Validate tracking

Font usage and tracking are independent. The lack of tracking won't block font rendering and the includsion of tracking will report font usage regardless of whether fonts are loading.

### Referencing Fonts

To use our self-hosted fonts add the following to your root variables file. Numbers with an `i` indicate you want the italic version.

```
$tp-include-fonts: '300', '300i', '400', '400i', '500', '500i';
```

### Tracking Fonts

We are required by our font license to track the fonts we use. Note that this reporting doesn't depend on fonts actually loading so be sure that the reported fonts match the fonts being used.

If you are using the six fonts listed above the following script will tracking for them.


```
<script type="text/javascript">
    var MTUserId='0910850a-71db-476e-83af-1574285881c5';
    var MTFontIds = new Array();

    MTFontIds.push("1129856"); // Avenir 300 Light
    MTFontIds.push("1129859"); // Avenir 300 Light Italic
    MTFontIds.push("721263"); // Avenir 400 Regular
    MTFontIds.push("721266"); // Avenir 400 Italic
    MTFontIds.push("721275"); // Avenir 500 Medium
    MTFontIds.push("721278"); // Avenir 500 Medium Italic

    (function() {
        var mtTracking = document.createElement('script');
        mtTracking.type='text/javascript';
        mtTracking.async='true';
        mtTracking.src='//thumbprint.thumbtack.com/asset/js/mtiFontTrackingCode.js';

        (document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0]||document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]).appendChild(mtTracking);
    })();
</script>
```

If you were loading all our fonts:

```
<script type="text/javascript">
    var MTUserId='0910850a-71db-476e-83af-1574285881c5';
    var MTFontIds = new Array();

    MTFontIds.push("1129856"); // Avenir 300 Light
    MTFontIds.push("1129859"); // Avenir 300 Light Italic
    MTFontIds.push("721263"); // Avenir 400 Regular
    MTFontIds.push("721266"); // Avenir 400 Italic
    MTFontIds.push("721275"); // Avenir 500 Medium
    MTFontIds.push("721278"); // Avenir 500 Medium Italic
    MTFontIds.push("721269"); // Avenir 600 Demi
    MTFontIds.push("721272"); // Avenir 600 Demi Italic
    MTFontIds.push("721281"); // Avenir 700 Bold
    MTFontIds.push("721284"); // Avenir 700 Bold Italic

    (function() {
        var mtTracking = document.createElement('script');
        mtTracking.type='text/javascript';
        mtTracking.async='true';
        mtTracking.src='//thumbprint.thumbtack.com/asset/js/mtiFontTrackingCode.js';

        (document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0]||document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]).appendChild(mtTracking);
    })();
</script>
```

### Validate Tracking

Check Chrome's console under `Network > CSS` and reload the page. One of the items listed should look similar to:

```
http://fast.fonts.net/lt/1.css?apiType=css&c=0910850a-71db-476e-83af-1574285881c5&fontids=1129856,1129859,721263,721266...
```

This is the output from the second javascript snippet above and indicates successful reporting.

