# `tp-ui-core-mixin`

## Import in your Sass file

To use Thumbprint UI mixins add the following import statement at the top of your Sass file.

```scss
@import '@thumbtack/tp-ui-core-mixin/_index';
```

## Responsive Mixin Usage

For responsive code we have three mixins. Because we are "mobile-first", `@include tp-respond-above($width)` should be used mostly commonly.

| mixin | width value options
|---|---|
| `@include tp-respond-above($width)` |  breakpoint variable or hard-coded value
| `@include tp-respond-below($width)` |  breakpoint variable or hard-coded value
| `@include tp-respond-between($min-width, $max-width)` |  breakpoint variable or hard-coded value

Breakpoint variables should be used unless there's an important reason to use hard-coded value.

- `$tp-breakpoint__small`
- `$tp-breakpoint__medium`
- `$tp-breakpoint__large`


With each mixin you can pass in a breakpoint variable, e.g., `$tp-breakpoint__small`, or a value, `540px`.

```scss
.my-component {    
    @include tp-respond-between($tp-breakpoint__small, $tp-breakpoint__medium) {
        color: blue;
    }
}

.my-component {    
    @include tp-respond-above(540px)  {
        color: blue;
    }
}

.my-component {    
    @include tp-respond-below($tp-breakpoint__large)  {
        color: blue;
    }
}
```
